  "contentHtml": "\n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Bengaluru: Medical device maker Medtronic said on Wednesday it plans to acquire privately held <a href=\"/tag/spr+therapeutics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SPR Therapeutics</a> for about $650 ‚ÄĆmillion in ‚Ā†cash, ‚Ā†expanding its portfolio of treatments for chronic pain.The ‚Äčdeal gives Medtronic access to SPR's SPRINT ‚Äčsystem, a 60-day ‚Ā†therapy designed ‚ÄĆto provide ‚Äčpain ‚Äčrelief withoutrequiring a permanent ‚Ā†implant.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>SPR Therapeutics is focused ‚Äčon non-opioid, non-surgical, minimally ‚Äčinvasive pain management solutions.Medtronic said the acquisition will help it reach ‚ÄĆmore patients with less invasive pain relief ‚Äčoptions.‚ÄčThe deal ‚Ā†is expected to close in the first half of Medtronic's ‚Äčfiscal 2027, which began on April 25, subject to regulatory approvals.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>(Reporting by Kunal Das in Bengaluru)                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                    \n\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/12345678/Reuters\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Reuters</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> U